author: Doug Buchanan
title: Who's coming to town in August: Cleveland Browns, Japanese anime, Gay Softball World Series, Republican presidential contenders
text: Website Cleveland Browns Orange & Brown Scrimmage What: The Cleveland Browns' first-ever scrimmage at Ohio Stadium, in front of a sold-out crowd. Dawg Pound Drive will take place before the scrimmage where fans can enjoy food, live music, alumni autographs, appearances from Brownie, Chomps & Swagger, giveaways and more from 3-6 p.m. outside St. John Arena. When: Aug. 7, from 6-8 p.m. Attendance: 60,000 Website Matsuricon What: An annual Japanese pop-culture event that focuses on Japanese animation (anime), Japanese graphic novels (manga), and video games. Its goal is to promote the cultural awareness of Japanese pop-culture through related events, special guest speakers and cultural presentations. When: Aug. 14-16
